<font color="#FF0000">-AND I STILL DON'T BELIEVE IT!</font><br>
<tt>Fri Aug  8 23:16:03 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Fierce opponents often have honor and are worthy. I have respect for a fierce worthy opponent, and will treat him appropriately, even if we must be locked in mortal combat.<br><br>
This is a very ancient way, born when all men were part of nature and life, rather than the newer way of dominance over nature and life.<br><br>
For fierce opponents without honor, and I have met a few of those from time to time, the not &quot;taking of a scalp&quot; is a very appropriate insult and statement on the worthlessness of that individual. He is clearly not worth bringing home, in any capacity. He is better left for the vultures and the worms. In that way, he is completely dishonored, and I retain my honor for more worthy foe.
<p><code>-- art16@ix.netcom.com  (Arthur Varanelli) </code><p>


